Definition: excessive sternness
Example: severity of character; the harshness of his punishment was inhuman; the rigors of boot camp
Synonyms: adj, all, nonindulgent, severe, severeness, harshness, unpleasant, harsh, disagreeable, rigor, demanding, rigorous, rigour, rigorousness, exact, rigourousness, inclemency, inclement, hardness, bad, hard, stiffness, sternness, excessive, of, character, the, his, punishment, was, inhuman, rigors, boot, camp
Category: noun.attribute
